38 //
39 // Defines the TrajectoryInterpreter class, which listens for new trajectory
40 // messages and, on a timer, repeatedly queries the current trajectory and
41 // publishes the corresponding reference.
42 //

64 template<typename S>
65 class TrajectoryInterpreter : private Uncopyable {
66 public:
67  ~TrajectoryInterpreter() {}
68  explicit TrajectoryInterpreter()
69  : initialized_(false) {}
70 
71  // Initialize this class with all parameters and callbacks.
72  bool Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
73 
74 private:
75  bool LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
76  bool RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n);
77 
78  // Callback for applying tracking controller.
79  void TimerCallback(const ros::TimerEvent& e);
80 
81  // Callback for processing trajectory updates.
82  inline void TrajectoryCallback(const fastrack_msgs::Trajectory::ConstPtr& msg) {
83  traj_ = Trajectory<S>(msg);
84  }
85 
86  // Process in flight notifications.
87  inline void InFlightCallback(const std_msgs::Empty::ConstPtr& msg) {
88  in_flight_ = true;
89  }
90 
91  // Current trajectory.
92  Trajectory<S> traj_;
93 
94  // Planner runtime -- how long does it take for the planner to run.
95  double planner_runtime_;
96 
97  // Set a recurring timer for a discrete-time controller.
98  ros::Timer timer_;
99  double time_step_;
100 
101  // Publishers/subscribers and related topics.
102  ros::Publisher bound_pub_;
103  ros::Publisher ref_pub_;
104  ros::Publisher request_traj_pub_;
105  ros::Publisher traj_vis_pub_;
106  ros::Subscriber traj_sub_;
107  ros::Subscriber in_flight_sub_;
108 
109  std::string bound_topic_;
110  std::string ref_topic_;
111  std::string request_traj_topic_;
112  std::string traj_vis_topic_;
113  std::string traj_topic_;
114  std::string in_flight_topic_;
115 
116  // Frames of reference for publishing markers.
117  std::string fixed_frame_id_;
118  std::string planner_frame_id_;
119 
120  // Transform broadcaster for planner position.
121  tf2_ros::TransformBroadcaster tf_broadcaster_;
122 
123  // Are we in flight?
124  bool in_flight_;
125 
126  // Naming and initialization.
127  std::string name_;
128  bool initialized_;
129 };

131 // ---------------------------- IMPLEMENTATION ------------------------------ //
132 
133 // Initialize this class with all parameters and callbacks.
134 template<typename S>
135 bool TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::Initialize(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
136  name_ = ros::names::append(n.getNamespace(), "TrajectoryInterpreter");
137 
138  // Load parameters.
139  if (!LoadParameters(n)) {
140  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to load parameters.", name_.c_str());
141  return false;
142  }
143 
144  // Register callbacks.
145  if (!RegisterCallbacks(n)) {
146  ROS_ERROR("%s: Failed to register callbacks.", name_.c_str());
147  return false;
148  }
149 
150  initialized_ = true;
151  return true;
152 }
153 
154 // Load parameters.
155 template<typename S>
156 bool TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::LoadParameters(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
157  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
158 
159  // Topics.
160  if (!nl.getParam("topic/in_flight", in_flight_topic_)) return false;
161  if (!nl.getParam("topic/traj", traj_topic_)) return false;
162  if (!nl.getParam("topic/ref", ref_topic_)) return false;
163  if (!nl.getParam("topic/request_traj", request_traj_topic_)) return false;
164  if (!nl.getParam("vis/traj", traj_vis_topic_)) return false;
165  if (!nl.getParam("vis/bound", bound_topic_)) return false;
166 
167  // Frames.
168  if (!nl.getParam("frame/fixed", fixed_frame_id_)) return false;
169  if (!nl.getParam("frame/planner", planner_frame_id_)) return false;
170 
171  // Time step.
172  if (!nl.getParam("time_step", time_step_)) return false;
173 
174  return true;
175 }
176 
177 // Register callbacks.
178 template<typename S>
179 bool TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::RegisterCallbacks(const ros::NodeHandle& n) {
180  ros::NodeHandle nl(n);
181 
182  // Subscribers.
183  in_flight_sub_ = nl.subscribe(in_flight_topic_.c_str(), 1,
184  &TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::InFlightCallback, this);
185 
186  traj_sub_ = nl.subscribe(traj_topic_.c_str(), 1,
187  &TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::TrajectoryCallback, this);
188 
189  // Publishers.
190  ref_pub_ = nl.advertise<fastrack_msgs::State>(ref_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
191 
192  request_traj_pub_ = nl.advertise<fastrack_msgs::ReplanRequest>(
193  request_traj_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
194 
195  bound_pub_ = nl.advertise<visualization_msgs::Marker>(
196  bound_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
197 
198  traj_vis_pub_ = nl.advertise<visualization_msgs::Marker>(
199  traj_vis_topic_.c_str(), 1, false);
200 
201  // Timer.
202  timer_ = nl.createTimer(ros::Duration(time_step_),
203  &TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::TimerCallback, this);
204 
205  return true;
206 }
207 
208 // Callback for applying tracking controller.
209 template<typename S>
210 void TrajectoryInterpreter<S>::TimerCallback(const ros::TimerEvent& e) {
211  if (traj_.Size() == 0) {
212  ROS_WARN_THROTTLE(1.0, "%s: No trajectory received.", name_.c_str());
213  return;
214  }
215 
216  // Interpolate the current trajectory.
217  const S planner_x = traj_.Interpolate(ros::Time::now().toSec());
218 
219  // Convert to ROS msg and publish.
220  ref_pub_.publish(planner_x.ToRos());
221 }
